<font color="#FF0000">RESPECT LIFE</font><br>
<tt>Tue Feb  4 17:11:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Having been a combat medic a lot of memories both good and not so good come and go like so many clouds on a warm summer day.  As I approach my 50th B-Day I look on Viet Nam as a learning and unlearning experience. What I learned from movies and TV as a kid growing up in the mid-west was not necessarily true. What I learned in the service was not necessarily true either. What I learned from the women and men I served with and from the men,women and children I served was that life is the most precious gift that we are given and it is treated as the most expendable resource on our planet. That is why I have chosen to treat other peoples lives with the respect that life deserves. I am now learning to feel that way about my own life which I have disregarded for over 30 years.<br>

